 "title": "Roosterkoek – braai treat",
 "excerpt": "You can buy ready-made dough at the shop and make roosterkoek from that. Still, there's something fulfilling about kneading your own dough. The same dough can also be used for vetkoek or for an ordinary loaf of bread. YOU NEED: 1kg flour (I used cake flour) 1 packet yeast …",
 "seo": {
  "title": "Roosterkoek - braai treat - Marinda Kook",
  "description": null
 },
 "html": "<p>You can buy ready-made dough at the shop and make roosterkoek from it.  Still, there's something fulfilling about kneading your own dough.  The same dough can also be used for vetkoek or for an ordinary loaf of bread.</p>\n<p>YOU NEED:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1kg flour ( I used cake flour)</li>\n<li>1 packet yeast (10g)<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-001.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1052\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 001\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-001-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>30ml sugar</li>\n<li>10 ml salt</li>\n<li>80 ml melted butter</li>\n<li>500 – 600 ml lukewarm water ( like a baby's bathwater)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>NOW:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>into a bowl pour the flour, yeast, sugar and salt and mix<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-009.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1053\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 009\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-009-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>stir the melted butter into your water</li>\n<li>now pour the water slowly into your flour</li>\n<li>and knead<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-010.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1054\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 010\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-010-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>and knead<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-012.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1055\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 012\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-012-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>and knead</li>\n<li>and knead until it becomes elastic ( about 10 minutes)<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-013.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1056\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 013\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-013-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>cover your dough with cling wrap in the bowl <a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-020.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1066\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 020\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-020-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>let it rise until double the volume<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-026.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1057\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 026\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-026-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>press your hands into flour and knock the dough down</li>\n<li>now shape the roosterkoek and place on a flat surface or tray – dip your hands in the flour regularly, because then you work better with the dough<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-034.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1059\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 034\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-034-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>cover with a cloth and let rise again<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-041.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1067\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 041\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-041-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>in the meantime you've made your fire and are ready to braai the roosterkoek</li>\n<li>braai it high up and very slowly<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-047.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1060\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 047\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-047-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n<li>if you knock it and it sounds hollow, then you know it's ready<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-073.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1064\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 073\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-073-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Roosterkoek needs a thick layer of butter.<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-053.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1061\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 053\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-053-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></p>\n<p>Roosterkoek can be eaten sweet or savoury.<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-058.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1062\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 058\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-058-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></p>\n<p>Tonight we had it with a thick layer of butter, mackataan and cheese.<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-070.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1063\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 070\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-070-1024x768.jpg\" width=\"1024\" height=\"768\"></a></p>\n<p>Absolutely delicious.<a href=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-054.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"aligncenter size-large wp-image-1065\" alt=\"roosterkoek blog 054\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/roosterkoek-blog-054-768x1024.jpg\" width=\"768\" height=\"1024\"></a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"
}
